6 h. A program for anger management, couples counseling, or
7 family and marital counseling shall not solely qualify
8 for the treatment requirement for domestic abuse
9 pursuant to this subsection. The counseling may be
10 ordered in addition to the treatment of domestic abuse
11 or per evaluation as set forth below. If, after
12 sufficient evaluation and attendance at required
13 treatment sessions, the domestic violence treatment
14 program determines that the defendant does not
15 evaluate as a perpetrator of domestic violence or does
16 evaluate as a perpetrator of domestic violence and
17 should complete other programs of treatment
18 simultaneously or prior to or subsequent to domestic
19 violence treatment, including, but not limited to,
20 programs related to the mental health, apparent
21 substance or alcohol abuse or inability or refusal to
22 manage anger, the defendant shall be ordered to
23 complete the counseling as per the recommendations of
24 the domestic violence treatment program;
